Sentencas: In order to improve the electrochemical performances of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC), La2Ni1-xO4 +/-delta (0.01 <= x <= 0.1) materials were prepared by citrate route and then used as cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: New La2Ni1-xO4±δ (0.01≤x≤0.1) Materials as Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Their microstructure and morphology were characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM), respectively.
Titulo: New La2Ni1-xO4±δ (0.01≤x≤0.1) Materials as Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The excess of the oxygen contents and the electrical conductivities were performed by iodometric titration and 4-point probs method respectively.
Titulo: New La2Ni1-xO4±δ (0.01≤x≤0.1) Materials as Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances were subsequently studied by impedance spectroscopy and the results obtained are promising which confirm the good electrochemical performance of most of the analyzed compositions.

Sentencas: It has been shown that, the electrical conductivity increases with increasing of the excess oxygen content.

Sentencas: The morphology of such cathode materials has a significant influence on the electrochemical behavior of the studied electrode materials.

Sentencas: Accordingly, among the studied materials, the Ni-10% deficient material (symbolised by LN10O) shows the best electrochemical properties with respect to oxygen reduction reaction.
